by scooter. I could definitely walk but it would take me about half an hour of walking. Thank goodness I learned to drive a scooter as a teenager, because here living off grid is a lot easier when you have mobility. Why? Because everything is so far away. A handful of plants in the yard may turn into landscaping, but if you expand further away for electricity, heat and maintenance supplies you will want a means of transportation. We have a lot of groceries with us, so we could probably last about 4-5 months without purchasing more getting more food if we had to.

This neighbor just built a huge lake. Unfortunately when you live off the grid, and are completely self-sufficient, its pretty hard to keep enclosed water such as black water, and gray water opaque. The family living below, got fed up with seeing their favorite water hole disappear, and created a very large lake that borders their property, so now I can stare at this lake while doing my dishes, and laundry as the views on the mountain are truly magical!

Here are a few people being screened before they enter the market.

The Food Store

When I say grocery store I mean the only grocery store that services the whole island. Meaning, there really is only one grocery in Saint Lucia. There are a few spin-off stores attached to it like wholesale, hardware, appliances, and etc. but we also order online from a place that ships from the States. My favorite website for ordering out of here is Amazon
